0: Couple rescued when car ends up 100 feet into ocean NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR First responders rescued two people whose car ended up more than 100 feet into the Atlantic Ocean. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR Firefighters were called to the Bernard Town Dock in Tremont, Maine, around 8 p.m. Tuesday after reports of two people trapped in a car in the water. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR Advertisement NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR Video from the incident shows extremely foggy conditions. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR The SUV was in 8 to 10 feet of water after traveling down a boat ramp and into the harbor, officials with the Tremont Volunteer Fire Department said. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR With the help of the Hancock County Deputy Sheriff and a fisherman, the rescuers were able to pull the couple onto a floating skiff. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR Crews then pulled the SUV back to shore and towed it away. Video showed water pouring out as it was brought back on land. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR An ambulance crew evaluated the couple. NEWLINE_CHAR NEWLINE_CHAR Several other people helped in the rescue, including the Southwest Harbor Fire Department, the harbormaster, other fishermen and the towing company.
